This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Science sub-category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) as it deals with website fingerprinting attacks on the Tor network. The use of deep learning also suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves network traffic analysis, which could place it in the sub-category of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). The use of deep learning for feature engineering also suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper involves image recognition techniques, which could place it in the sub-category of Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV).
